pyferm (0.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  The firewall service is NOT enabled or started automatically on install
  (anti-lockout). This differs from setups where the previous ferm unit was
  enabled: after installing pyferm your rules will not be applied on the next
  reboot until you opt in explicitly.

  Review /etc/ferm/ferm.conf, add your services under /etc/ferm/ferm.d/, then:

      systemctl enable --now ferm

  The shipped default blocks all inbound traffic except SSH (port 22 by the
  name "ssh") and ICMP. If SSH runs on a non-standard port, set $SSH_PORT in
  /etc/ferm/ferm.conf BEFORE enabling the service, or you will be locked out.

 -- Boris Talovikov <boris@talovikov.ru>  Tue, 16 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
